<!-- The source SCC in the condensation graph always has the largest finishing time. -->

Step 1
Run DFS.
Record finishing order.
Usually we push nodes onto a stack.

dfs(node){
    visited[node]=true;
    ...
    stack.push(node);
}

Why push after DFS finishes?
Because the node with the largest finishing time ends up on top.
Exactly what we want.

Step 2
Reverse every edge.
Suppose
0 → 1
becomes
1 → 0
Very simple.

Step 3
Clear
visited[]

Step 4
Pop nodes from the stack.
For every unvisited node,
run DFS on the reversed graph.
Every DFS gives exactly
One SCC.
Done.

DFS
↓
Stack (finishing order)
↓
Reverse Graph
↓
DFS using stack order
↓
Count SCCs

